:28:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1065.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Roleplaying a druid</span><hr size=1> Just wondering...how hard of a character do you think an evil druid would be?  I mean...not alignment neutral, isn't in the rules, but a druid with some evil tendecies...bad faction in good cities, maybe good faction somewhere so I can still bank and buy/sell...living mostly in the woods...hating all races for their exploitation of nature and only befriending more nature friendly classes...<br>
<br>
I was just thinking that it might be fun to try and roleplay, but then again, would anyone roleplay with me?  Hunh.  *shrugs*<br>
<br>
Thoughts? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usarhea.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sarhea</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 308<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/9/02 1:08:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1065.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Roleplaying a druid</span><hr size=1> *grin* well, having through the course of my stay here on FV, played an &quot;unkempt&quot; ranger, I don't thinkit'd be that hard. What I'm dying to see though is someone play a druid as the true neutral ya'll get stuck with. That's hard.*grin*<br>
<br>
I think playing otuside what people would expect can be very very fun, and lead to really cool things, myself*Smile* <p><center><b><A href="http://pub15.ezboard.com/bsarscorner"><font color="#710672" face="Black Chancery" size="-1">Sarhea </font></a>
</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umadrain.showPublicProfile?language=EN>madrain</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kerran Lord</span><br>  Posts: 146<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/9/02 1:31:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1065.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Roleplaying a druid</span><hr size=1> Well, it's just that I'm worried I'll be forced to solo.  I do enjoy soloing sometimes, but other times I do like to group, and I'm afraid that I'll have to either bend my own roleplaying rules to fit in a group or just go my own way.  Good guilds won't want me because of my views and bad faction, Neutral guilds probably wouldn't fit my viewpoint (neither would good, I'm thinking), and Evil guilds will probably not be very accomodating without some shoehorning or some very convincing roleplaying.<br>
<br>
It's just a thought I'm throwing around at the moment...a bearded human (bearded!) druid, sort of crazy or paranoid...I'm having alot of fun with my DE Shadowknight at the moment though, so we'll see how it turns out.<br>
<br>
Thanks for commenting Sarhea!  Anyone else?  Thoughts? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=wessley>Wessley</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/9/02 2:12:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1065.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> true neutral</span><hr size=1> I try to play my character as true neutral with flaws.  He was raised around elves so he has the influence of good, but he knows the laws of balance.  For instance, he doesn't change opinions of someone based on their race...but when a troll starts talking about elven slaves and such, Wessley tends to grind his teeth in frustration at not being able to do anything.  Sometimes frustration gets the better of him, sometimes not... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usarhea.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sarhea</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 309<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/9/02 2:55:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1065.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Roleplaying a druid</span><hr size=1> As far as grouping goes, it may take a bit of ingenuity, but you can find folks to hunt with. And as for guilds that may be a bit tougher. And my only other advice is not to be too surprised if your character goes places you hadn't expected, let me tell ya*grin* <p><center><b><A href="http://pub15.ezboard.com/bsarscorner"><font color="#710672" face="Black Chancery" size="-1">Sarhea </font></a>
</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukentassolgaard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kentas Solgaard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Eats Halflings</span><br>  Posts: 143<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/9/02 4:09:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1065.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.personal.psu.edu/students/b/t/btk120/MOKONA.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Hmm.</span><hr size=1> Roleplaying an Evil Druid can be a pain with all the faction problems that come in.<br>
<br>
However, wolf form will get you a lot of places.  You can eventually walk around most of Oggok (the place I've seen it done most) without needing your illusion.<br>
<br>
Hints:   3 froglok pickles and 10gp, or bits and pieces for the  Stein of Moggok.<br>
<br>
Eating 'lesser' races, hiding the fact you're warmly to the paladins in North Freeport, and being rude to some of the more good of the light races are plusses.<br>
<br>
Roleplaying a true neutral druid can be easy and it can be difficult.  The easy way is to be extremely apathetic. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   The hard way is to attempt balance--if you're killing the aviaks one day, maybe you'll kill the goblins the next for encroaching on the lands the aviaks had before you killed a bunch of them.<br>
<br>
 <p>--Antoin Nolouj &lt;League of Shadows&gt;
